descript.abstract: Zoning of the City of El Paso
descript.purpose: Used for producing official zoning maps and for land use analysis.
descript.supplinf: Please refer to the El Paso Municipal Code, Title 20 Zoning, for definitions of the various types of Zoning.

stdorder.ordering: Users can navigate online to www.PDNMapa.org where they can view current city zoning on the map viewer

altsys.altenc: Explicit elevation coordinate included with horizontal coordinates

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Full Zoning with spaces and hyphens
Zoning w/o conditions, contracts, or others shown
A C in this field means that the area covered by the polygon contains a condition/s
An SC in this field means that the area covered by the polygon contains a special contract/s
An SP in this field means that the area covered by the polygon contains a special permit/s
An H in this field means that the area covered by the polygon is zoned historic
An NCO in this field means that the area covered by the polygon contains a Non Conforming condition/s
Contains the date of the last zoning ordinance passed for that particular polygon
